4. Sandwiches with red fish, caviar and lemon oil



lenyvavsha / Depositphotos.com


Ingredients

¬Ω loaf or loaf of white bread;
100-150 g of red fish;
1 lemon;
100 g butter;
red caviar - to taste;
halibut caviar - to taste;
several branches of dill.

Cooking
Cut bread and fish into slices. Remove the zest from the lemon and grate it on a fine grater. Squeeze 2 tablespoons of lemon juice from the pulp.
Soften the oil at room temperature. Beat in a blender with zest and juice.
Grease each slice of bread with lemon oil. Put fish and caviar on top. Garnish with greens.
