8. Sandwiches with red fish and eggs



timolina / Depositphotos.com


Ingredients

2 quail or regular eggs;
100-150 g of red fish;
1-2 branches of dill or other herbs;
4 slices of bread;
3 tablespoons of cottage cheese.

Cooking
Hard-boiled eggs. Cut the fish into small pieces, divide the eggs into halves. Grind greens.
Slices of bread with cheese. Put fish and egg halves on top. Sprinkle with herbs.
