10. Sandwiches with red fish and egg salad


Foodnetwork.com

Ingredients

12 eggs;
2-3 branches of dill;
80 g mayonnaise;
2 teaspoons granular mustard;
1 teaspoon of salt;
¬Ω teaspoon ground black pepper;
8 slices of bread;
8 slices of red fish.

Cooking
Hard-boiled eggs. Cool, peel and chop finely with a knife or in a food processor. Grind dill, leave a little for decoration.
Combine mayonnaise with eggs, mustard, dill, salt and pepper.
Put a piece of fish on each slice of bread, and egg salad on top. Garnish with greens.
